review_blob: good for a mexican beer.  Better than corona.  nice balance to the salsa and fajitas i was eating.  very light

This is my favorite beer when I can get to Kansas.  Its probably a good thing that I dont have easier access to it.  Very refreshing and as others have mentioned, it is smooth.  Get some if you can....
Good as an everyday beer.  No big deal though. To me it tastes like Negra Modelo.
I think this is the worst beer available. And to  think I paid 8 bucks for a cup of it at a St. Louis Cardinal game.  Still better than a coke or Dr. Pepper...
When I want to think about how a beer tastes, I dont reach for a Coors.  But it is what it is.  There arent many better beers to drink when its hot outside, or when playing golf......

Lots of yeasty taste, almost like eating bread.  I have had this on tap and was quite pleased.  In a bottle the head was very thin and not nearly as tasty.  I wouldnt turn it down, but probably wouldnt buy more.
Pours nice with a thinnish head.  In many respects is like Shiner Bock.  A good average beer.
I had never had a porter before this....definitely liked this one.  Very dark color.  Combines my 3 favorites, chocolate, coffee, and beer.  Highly recommended
Easy to drink.  I had just played golf and was thirsty, but overall I liked it.  Better than the usual available around here.
